# Q2 Migration Schedule Critical-Paths Through Database Cutover

```mermaid
gantt
    title Q2 2026 Migration Schedule
    dateFormat  YYYY-MM-DD
    axisFormat  %b %d

    section Discovery
    Audit existing schema       :done,    a1, 2026-04-01, 7d
    Map consumer dependencies   :done,    a2, after a1, 5d

    section Build
    Compatibility shim          :active,  b1, 2026-04-13, 10d
    Migration scripts           :         b2, after b1, 14d
    Rollback procedures         :         b3, after b1, 7d

    section Cutover
    Staging dry-run             :crit,    c1, after b2, 3d
    Production cutover          :crit,    c2, after c1, 1d
    Soak window                 :         c3, after c2, 7d

    section Cleanup
    Remove shim                 :         d1, after c3, 5d
    Archive old schema          :         d2, after d1, 3d
```

Source: migration plan v3, owned by Platform team. Critical path runs through
"Migration scripts" → "Staging dry-run" → "Production cutover". Each delay on
those bars pushes the cutover date by the same amount.

Use this format for surfaces that auto-render mermaid (GitHub, GitLab, Notion,
Obsidian, recent VS Code). For surfaces that do not, use the `.html.tmpl` variant.
